content: The new benchmarks don't seem to be showing the comparison page. They seem to be running (according to the status page), but when viewing the comparison page for PRs where the new benchmarks were run (here), they don't seem to show up. Why would this be?
Looks like the API is serving them so we must be filtering in the frontend. I'll take a look

I think it's because the benchmarks were not run on one of the two artifacts being compared (though I thought that was the case). I believe the next time a perf run is done at least the cranelift-codegen-0.82.1 data should show up
This is indeed the case, and the new benchmarks are now showing up!
